# Trivy ignore rules for AWS Free Tier project
# These are intentional trade-offs: each fix would incur costs that conflict
# with the free-tier goal.

# Aurora: storage_encrypted = true uses AWS-managed key (free).
# CMK would add ~$1/month in KMS charges.
AWS-0079

# CloudFront: WAF is not free-tier eligible.
AWS-0011

# S3: AES256 (SSE-S3) is free. SSE-KMS with a CMK would add KMS charges.
AWS-0132

# EC2: unrestricted egress is standard for a web server that needs to pull
# packages. Restricting egress would require a NAT gateway ($32/month) or
# VPC endpoints (not free).
AWS-0104

# SNS: topic encryption requires a KMS key, which is not free-tier.
AWS-0095
